Enum Class EventType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<EventType>
MVC.simu.model.EventType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<EventType>, Constable, IEventType
public enum EventType extends Enum<EventType> implements IEventType
Represents the different types of events that can occur in the visa/immigration application processing simulation.

This enum implements IEventType and categorizes events in the workflow, including system entry, service completion, system exit, and conditional events. Each event has a human-readable description and can be mapped to a specific service point in the processing workflow.

Event categories:

  • System entry events: ARRIVAL, REAPPLICATION
  • Service completion events: END_APPLICATION_ENTRY, END_DOC_SUBMISSION, END_BIOMETRICS, END_DOC_CHECK, END_DECISION
  • System exit events: EXIT_APPROVED, EXIT_REJECTED
  • Conditional events: MISSING_DOCS_RESOLVED, END_BIOMETRICS
See IEventType

    • isServiceCompletion

      public boolean isServiceCompletion()
      Determines if this event represents the completion of a service at a service point.

      Service completion events start with "END_" but exclude END_DECISION, which requires special handling.

      Returns:
      true if this event represents service completion, false otherwise

    • isSystemEntry

      public boolean isSystemEntry()
      Determines if this event represents an entry point into the system.

      System entry events are new applications arriving or reapplications being resubmitted to the system.

      Returns:
      true if this event marks system entry, false otherwise

    • isSystemExit

      public boolean isSystemExit()
      Determines if this event represents an exit from the system.

      System exit events occur when an application either receives final approval or rejection and leaves the workflow.

      Returns:
      true if this event marks system exit, false otherwise

    • isConditionalEvent

      public boolean isConditionalEvent()
      Determines if this event is conditional and may require additional processing or routing decisions.

      Conditional events include biometrics completion and missing documents resolution, which may result in different workflow paths.

      Returns:
      true if this event is conditional, false otherwise

    • getServicePointIndex

      public int getServicePointIndex()
      Maps this event type to the corresponding service point index in the workflow.

      Service points (0-5) correspond to:

      • 0: SP1 - Application Entry invalid input: '&' Appointment Booking
      • 1: SP2 - Document Submission Room
      • 2: SP3 - Biometrics Room
      • 3: SP4 - Missing Docs Waiting Room
      • 4: SP5 - Document Check Room
      • 5: SP6 - Decision Room
      Returns:
      the service point index (0-5) if associated, or -1 if not associated with a specific service point

    • getServicePointName

      public String getServicePointName()
      Returns a human-friendly Service Point name for this event.

      The name is retrieved from the SERVICE_POINT_NAMES array using the service point index. This provides a descriptive name for display purposes in the UI or reports.

      Returns:
      a descriptive service point name if this event is associated with a service point, or null if the event is not associated with a specific service point
